{"key":"processedPost-16145115","value":{"id":16145115,"first":16144683,"last":16145241,"when":1335504281,"utime":"04/27/12 08:24 AM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>Penis Envious said:</strong><br />Well I just read a thread yesterday, and the topic was the \"correct\" way to harvest. The consensus throughout the thread was that twisting and pulling is the correct way to harvest, because cutting at the base has the potential to cause contamination.</blockquote><br />That's a myth spread by people with no experience whatsoever.&nbsp; Bad info like that is the reason we had to come up with the <a href=\"/forums/showflat.php/Number/8903929#8903929\" class=\"pp\" target=\"_blank\">trusted cultivator tag</a>.&nbsp; If the mushrooms are loose and about to fall over, it doesn't do much damage to twist and pull.&nbsp; If they're firmly attached, you'll pull a chunk of substrate out with the base, and this WILL be a site for mold to get started.&nbsp; Slice fruits off at the base with a sharp knife.<br />RR"}}